reviews.text: Nice Trains... Think they could step up the regularity a bit by a few mins
Lack of lift makes it limited for parents of young children to use this place, which is same as most tube stations. There's no escalator, strictly stairs and it's quite steep.
When I finally regained consciousness, my only recollection was of being in a forest clearing, with stags and deer standing on their hind legs, engaged in a primitive form of dance.

Great station! Friendly staff. Always greeted in the morning by the gentlemen by the barriers, and the lovely lady on the platform heading northbound. Always there to help people.

The only frustration is the train itself. It can get extremely busy and on a couple of occasions, I've been unable to get on the train. Hopefully that will change when the new 4 carriage trains come along.
